programme.desc: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New England Patriots at U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis, which last hosted in 1992. Justin Timberlake performs at halftime. Bill Belichick's Patriots bid for a record-tying sixth Super Bowl win, while Philly chases its first, having last appeared 13 years ago in a 24-21 loss to New England. Deion Branch was MVP of that game, with QB Tom Brady taking MVP honors in the other four Pats wins. Tight ends Rob Gronkowski (Pats) and Zach Ertz (Eagles) are key scoring threats. (cc)(n)
